cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the problem of storing and delivering content in a wireless network, which is a typical problem in the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves coding techniques (MDS coding) and optimization algorithms (distributed approximation algorithm), which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also considers user mobility, which is a key aspect of control systems (cs.SY) and data science (cs.DS).
